column5: (ID Units:  SF: ) A well-known value 120.  Uniquely identifies this as a SunSpec Nameplate Model - Range: 120
(L Units: Registers SF: ) Length of Nameplate Model - Range: 26
(DERTyp Units:  SF: ) Type of DER device. Default value is 4 to indicate PV device. - Range: 4
(WRtg Units: W SF: WRtg_SF) Continuous power output capability of the inverter. - Range:
(WRtg_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor - Range: 0
(VARtg Units: VA SF: VARtg_SF) Continuous Volt-Ampere capability of the inverter. - Range:
(VARtg_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor - Range: 0
(VArRtgQ1 Units: var SF: VArRtg_SF) Continuous VAR capability of the inverter in quadrant 1. - Range:
(VArRtgQ2 Units: var SF: VArRtg_SF) Continuous VAR capability of the inverter in quadrant 2. - Range: Not supported
(VArRtgQ3 Units: var SF: VArRtg_SF) Continuous VAR capability of the inverter in quadrant 3. - Range: Not supported
(VArRtgQ4 Units: var SF: VArRtg_SF) Continuous VAR capability of the inverter in quadrant 4. - Range:
(VArRtg_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor - Range: 1
(ARtg Units: A SF: ARtg_SF) Maximum RMS AC current level capability of the inverter. - Range:
(ARtg_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor - Range: -2
(PFRtgQ1 Units: cos() SF: PFRtg_SF) Minimum power factor capability of the inverter in quadrant 1. - Range:
(PFRtgQ2 Units: cos() SF: PFRtg_SF) Minimum power factor capability of the inverter in quadrant 2. - Range: Not supported
(PFRtgQ3 Units: cos() SF: PFRtg_SF) Minimum power factor capability of the inverter in quadrant 3. - Range: Not supported
(PFRtgQ4 Units: cos() SF: PFRtg_SF) Minimum power factor capability of the inverter in quadrant 4. - Range:
(PFRtg_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor - Range: -3
(WHRtg Units: Wh SF: WHRtg_SF) Nominal energy rating of storage device. - Range:
(WHRtg_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor - Range: 0
(AhrRtg Units: AH SF: AhrRtg_SF) The useable capacity of the battery.  Maximum charge minus minimum charge from a technology capability perspective (Amp-hour capacity rating). - Range: Not supported
(AhrRtg_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor for amp-hour rating. - Range: Not supported
(MaxChaRte Units: W SF: MaxChaRte_SF) Maximum rate of energy transfer into the storage device. - Range:
(MaxChaRte_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor - Range: 0
(MaxDisChaRte Units: W SF: MaxDisChaRte_SF) Maximum rate of energy transfer out of the storage device. - Range:
(MaxDisChaRte_SF Units:  SF: ) Scale factor - Range: 0
(Pad Units:  SF: ) Pad register - Range:
